<br>
Why not get a list of entities that have actually killed a God. If the guild who is up, has not killed the God, let BB send as many as need from the start. The less experienced guild would then learn from people who &quot;should&quot; know what they are doing.<br>
<br>
The BB guild that is up, should take initiative to get in touch with the guild in the plane. Verify that they can, or cannot kill the God, then notify the Admins of the situation. <br>
<br>
This should make a 2am finish very achievable.<br>
2am will be documented as the end of a raid no matter what. If the BB does not get the kill within that time frame, the next BB  is up. No excuses. Server drops, tough luck, those are the breaks. <br>
<br>
<br>
New rule: BB can NOT be called in the day before they have a Plane.. We can call this the FR rule.<br>
<br>
New rule: BB can not be in the plane on God days if a capable guild is in the Plane. If a BB member has a trade arranged, he will wait outside till the God is dead.<br>
<br>
New rule: Sky will support Fri/Sat raids for people going to the top. Sat/Sun raids for people staying below. The Admins will determine if you are capable to reserve Friday starts.<br>
<br>
New rule: Anyone breaking the rules will lose 1 raid on 1st offense. 2nd offense 45 days no posting rights. 3rd offense banned from The Rathe calendar for 90 days.<br>
<br>
Entities must be held accountable for breaking the rules. If not then we cannot have a Calendar.<br>
<br>
We need to have a rules enforcement commitee. Need some ideas on who should be on this commitee. Maybe 50+ member entities get 1 rep?<br>
<br>
I think I have covered most sticking points in getting this agreement done. <br>
