<br>
Having a hard set end time of 2am PST.  I don't like this, but *if* the Epic is called NLT 8pm PST, I can see it.  However, what about those situations where at 8pm, everything is going well, but by 10pm it's gone to hell in a handbasket?  The posting entity can, and should, call Epic, but will there be enough time to get stuff done?  Let the posting entity, Epic, and next days raid talk.  See if something can be worked out for Epic to stay later (no more than 2 hours).<br>
<br>
Epic cannot be called-in if they have the plane the next day.  Why?  Allow this, but stipulate that regardless how late it runs, that the posting entity gets the god loot, minus any epic item for Epic.<br>
<br>
Members of an Epic not on call in the plane when a god is up.  Change this to no more than 2 invites.<br>
<br>
Sky piggyback.  Allow any entity to post for Fri/Sat; however, if the entity does not get past Isle 4 on Fri, and the entity behind them will, the first entity jumps.  Even experienced entities who have accomplished getting thru Sky can have problems, and *could* interfere with the entity coming up behind them breathing down their necks.<br>
<br>
As for punishments, a precedent has already been set.  Solorees was bound and determined to get his guild thru the plane and slay CT, but did not, and did not call-in Epic.  After extensive conversation, they were suspended from posting for 30 days (tho they did keep their Hate raid). <p><center><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="5" color="#C0C0C0"><strong>Edwina Nytengayle<br> </strong></font></center>

